f:png\u002FczM6Ly9jb2hvc3QtcHJvZC9hdHRhY2htZW50LzE5ZWVmNDUzLTVkNzUtNDNlZi1hNGQzLTdmMmI1NjJiODA4NC9qb3N0bGVzb3J0LmdpZg","fileURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002F19eef453-5d75-43ef-a4d3-7f2b562b8084\u002Fjostlesort.gif","kind":"image","width":162,"height":162}},{"type":"attachment","attachment":{"attachmentId":"7bd35c07-70b6-4890-a2f2-619922596793","altText":"I just needed something here so the gif wasn't massive lol. It's my profile icon, but it's been sorted, so it looks kinda weird. Dist\"sorted\", if you will","previewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002F7bd35c07-70b6-4890-a2f2-619922596793\u002FLQ9Tz7Q.png","fileURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002F7bd35c07-70b6-4890-a2f2-619922596793\u002FLQ9Tz7Q.png","kind":"image","width":399,"height":400}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"*(Before I explain - I had **5 megabytes** to compress a gif of literal noise haha, so please forgive how absolutely crunchy it is. Below is a much higher quality video version!)*"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Ok, so here's the problem:\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHow do you sort a 2D array in 2 dimensions at once?\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"For example, in the above gif, I'm sorting both **hue** and **lightness** to make the final rainbow. Sounds simple to sort, until you consider two issues:\n1. You have to stick to the grid - you can't double up pixels.\n2. In normal situations, you'll have data that skews to certain hues."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"The real-world scenario I encountered this in was my desire to **sort player-made characters in a grid, by color**. I can *plot* them by color, and I can place them in a grid *arbitrarily*, but how can I do both?"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"\u003Cdiv style=\"display: flex;\"\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\"flex-grow: calc(1920 \u002F 1080); display: block; flex-basis: 0px; width: 0px; height: auto;\"\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd45e7dc1-4af1-4447-96c7-f3e0a420f50d\u002FLUrTOov.png\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd45e7dc1-4af1-4447-96c7-f3e0a420f50d\u002FLUrTOov.png\" alt=\"A large image of 6951 pixel art characters, sorted by color. The characters are overlapping and clumped.\" title=\"A large image of 6951 pixel art characters, sorted by color. The characters are overlapping and clumped.\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\"\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\"flex-grow: calc(1920 \u002F 1080); display: block; flex-basis: 0px; width: 0px; height: auto;\"\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd156288a-d135-4dc0-a8eb-2523225303fd\u002FDCc0STf.png\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd156288a-d135-4dc0-a8eb-2523225303fd\u002FDCc0STf.png\" alt=\"A perfect grid of 6954 pixel art characters, with no obvious sorting.\" title=\"A perfect grid of 6954 pixel art characters, with no obvious sorting.\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\"\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Zoom in - that's 6,954 player-made skins for my game \u003Ca href='https:\u002F\u002Fmineblocks.com\u002F1'\u003EMine Blocks\u003C\u002Fa\u003E! ❤)\u003C\u002Fem\u003E"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"The solution I ended up with is what I call **JostleSort™**:\n* I swap pixels with their nearby neighbors if doing so would make them more sorted.\n* The swapping occurs further away if the pixel thinks it's less sorted.\n* It \"jostles\" it around a bit, like sifting sand, in order to avoid local minima and stalemates."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"My solution is honestly very slow, and it feels like a brute force solution. But I can't think of a better way to do it... \u003Cstrong\u003Ecan you think of any ideas?\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Here's a much higher quality video than the first one *(if you're on desktop at least; on mobile, Streamable compresses it a lot more)*, however I must warn you: tragically, it ends too early! Unfortunately I had to stop it so I could sleep."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"https:\u002F\u002Fstreamable.com\u002Fq664a"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"*For further research: the general problem in this post is one of [dimensionality reduction](https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FDimensionality_reduction). My concept feels similar to [gradient descent](https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FGradient_descent), but... nothing seems to consider sorting things in a packed 2D array?*"}}],"plainTextBody":"*(Before I explain - I had **5 megabytes** to compress a gif of literal noise haha, so please forgive how absolutely crunchy it is. Below is a much higher quality video version!)*\n\nOk, so here's the problem:\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHow do you sort a 2D array in 2 dimensions at once?\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\n\nFor example, in the above gif, I'm sorting both **hue** and **lightness** to make the final rainbow. Sounds simple to sort, until you consider two issues:\n1. You have to stick to the grid - you can't double up pixels.\n2. In normal situations, you'll have data that skews to certain hues.\n\nThe real-world scenario I encountered this in was my desire to **sort player-made characters in a grid, by color**. I can *plot* them by color, and I can place them in a grid *arbitrarily*, but how can I do both?\n\n\u003Cdiv style=\"display: flex;\"\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\"flex-grow: calc(1920 \u002F 1080); display: block; flex-basis: 0px; width: 0px; height: auto;\"\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd45e7dc1-4af1-4447-96c7-f3e0a420f50d\u002FLUrTOov.png\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd45e7dc1-4af1-4447-96c7-f3e0a420f50d\u002FLUrTOov.png\" alt=\"A large image of 6951 pixel art characters, sorted by color. The characters are overlapping and clumped.\" title=\"A large image of 6951 pixel art characters, sorted by color. The characters are overlapping and clumped.\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\"\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\"flex-grow: calc(1920 \u002F 1080); display: block; flex-basis: 0px; width: 0px; height: auto;\"\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd156288a-d135-4dc0-a8eb-2523225303fd\u002FDCc0STf.png\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fattachment\u002Fd156288a-d135-4dc0-a8eb-2523225303fd\u002FDCc0STf.png\" alt=\"A perfect grid of 6954 pixel art characters, with no obvious sorting.\" title=\"A perfect grid of 6954 pixel art characters, with no obvious sorting.\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\"\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003C\u002Fdiv\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Zoom in - that's 6,954 player-made skins for my game \u003Ca href='https:\u002F\u002Fmineblocks.com\u002F1'\u003EMine Blocks\u003C\u002Fa\u003E! ❤)\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\n\nThe solution I ended up with is what I call **JostleSort™**:\n* I swap pixels with their nearby neighbors if doing so would make them more sorted.\n* The swapping occurs further away if the pixel thinks it's less sorted.\n* It \"jostles\" it around a bit, like sifting sand, in order to avoid local minima and stalemates.\n\nMy solution is honestly very slow, and it feels like a brute force solution. But I can't think of a better way to do it... \u003Cstrong\u003Ecan you think of any ideas?\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\n\nHere's a much higher quality video than the first one *(if you're on desktop at least; on mobile, Streamable compresses it a lot more)*, however I must warn you: tragically, it ends too early! Unfortunately I had to stop it so I could sleep.\n\nhttps:\u002F\u002Fstreamable.com\u002Fq664a\n\n*For further research: the general problem in this post is one of [dimensionality reduction](https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FDimensionality_reduction). My concept feels similar to [gradient descent](https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FGradient_descent), but... nothing seems to consider sorting things in a packed 2D array?*","postingProject":{"projectId":38578,"handle":"zanzlanz","displayName":"Zanzlanz","dek":"Game developer and music producer!","description":"---\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nAt this point, my posts are a very condensed way to get to know what I do and have done, so please browse!\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nIn general, I make all sorts of **games** and **music** and **other creative stuff**!\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nBtw, [wetclap.com](https:\u002F\u002Fwetclap.com) :]","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F38578-15d4f3c9-8d88-47b6-817d-8fc6d35b361a-profile.jpg","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F38578-15d4f3c9-8d88-47b6-817d-8fc6d35b361a-profile.jpg","headerURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fheader\u002F38578-87906878-de99-477f-a422-e3a7345598fe-profile.jpg","headerPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fheader\u002F38578-87906878-de99-477f-a422-e3a7345598fe-profile.jpg","privacy":"public","url":"http:\u002F\u002Ftwitter.com\u002Fzanzlanz","pronouns":"he\u002Fhim","flags":[],"avatarShape":"circle","loggedOutPostVisibility":"public","frequentlyUsedTags":["gamedev","generative art","pixelart"],"askSettings":{"enabled":false,"allowAnon":false,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null},"shareTree":[],"numSharedComments":0,"relatedProjects":[],"singlePostPageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.o