\"column\":136,\"offset\":2654}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\", however I must warn you: tragically, it ends too early! Unfortunately I had to stop it so I could sleep.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":25,\"column\":136,\"offset\":2654},\"end\":{\"line\":25,\"column\":242,\"offset\":2760}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":25,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2519},\"end\":{\"line\":25,\"column\":242,\"offset\":2760}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fstreamable.com\u002Fq664a\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fstreamable.com\u002Fq664a\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2762},\"end\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":29,\"offset\":2790}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2762},\"end\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":29,\"offset\":2790}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2762},\"end\":{\"line\":27,\"column\":29,\"offset\":2790}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"em\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"For further research: the general problem in this post is one of \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":2,\"offset\":2793},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":67,\"offset\":2858}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FDimensionality_reduction\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"dimensionality reduction\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":68,\"offset\":2859},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":92,\"offset\":2883}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":67,\"offset\":2858},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":149,\"offset\":2940}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\". My concept feels similar to \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":149,\"offset\":2940},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":179,\"offset\":2970}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FGradient_descent\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"gradient descent\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":180,\"offset\":2971},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":196,\"offset\":2987}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":179,\"offset\":2970},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":245,\"offset\":3036}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\", but... nothing seems to consider sorting things in a packed 2D array?\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":245,\"offset\":3036},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":316,\"offset\":3107}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2792},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":317,\"offset\":3108}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2792},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":317,\"offset\":3108}}}],\"data\":{\"quirksMode\":false},\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":29,\"column\":317,\"offset\":3108}}}"}],"readMoreIndex":null},"responseToAskId":null},"comments":{"406823":[{"comment":{"commentId":"95cf6246-6002-449a-8bd9-c0a120c734f5","postedAtISO":"2022-11-22T15:36:08.126Z","deleted":false,"body":"This probably isn't optimal, but here's a sketch of something that might be fast \u002F flexible enough if you have some extra memory space. If you sort all of the points by luminance (let's say hue for columns and luminance for rows) you can then 1) decide on the dimensions of your grid (say n columns x m rows), take the lowest n luminance values and sort them by hue, and write that into column 1, and keep going. That'll be pretty fast since the inner sorts are quicker than sorting the whole list twice. Will it work for your application?\n\nI suspect if you know the dimensions of your grid in advance you can get something much better, basically \"plot everything into rectangular buckets and then solve a problem with the buckets\".","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"fa8fd4a1-5923-4dde-a7fe-fb270042dde3","postedAtISO":"2022-11-22T16:24:26.916Z","deleted":false,"body":"Oh those ideas get me thinking, thanks! I wonder what an approach that uses quad trees would look like; I can't seem to wrap my mind around relating this problem to traditional sorting algorithms, because elements will get stuck depending on which axis you're sorting on. For example if you sort horizontally and vertically a bunch of times, you get little + signs","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"9bb16ec7-51bc-4b07-8f8d-151aaaebee5b","postedAtISO":"2022-11-23T07:21:41.485Z","deleted":false,"body":"If you do multiple sorting passes over the same data you should look into using a stable sorting algorithm. Unstable sorting can mess up the previous sorting passes.\n\nI don't think the approach of @joeatwork would be affected by that, because it divides the list up into sublists, but it is something to look out for.","children":[],"postId":406823,"inReplyTo":"fa8fd4a1-5923-4dde-a7fe-fb270042dde3","hasCohostPlus":false,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":30994,"handle":"Pseudoradius","displayName":"","dek":"","description":"","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Frc\u002Fdefault-avatar\u002F30994.png","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Frc\u002Fdefault-avatar\u002F30994.png","headerURL":null,"headerPreviewURL":null,"privacy":"public","url":null,"pronouns":null,"flags":[],"avatarShape":"circle","loggedOutPostVisibility":"public","frequentlyUsedTags":[],"askSettings":{"enabled":false,"allowAnon":false,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null}}],"postId":406823,"inReplyTo":"95cf6246-6002-449a-8bd9-c0a120c734f5","hasCohostP