hostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F66739-f91bdfdb-8757-499a-8483-35e15119f390-profile.png","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F66739-f91bdfdb-8757-499a-8483-35e15119f390-profile.png","headerURL":null,"headerPreviewURL":null,"privacy":"public","url":"","pronouns":"any pronouns","flags":[],"avatarShape":"circle","loggedOutPostVisibility":"none","frequentlyUsedTags":[],"askSettings":{"enabled":true,"allowAnon":true,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[{"service":"Discord handle","value":"overnecked","visibility":"public"}],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null}},{"comment":{"commentId":"1f5c0ceb-e168-4353-b9dc-fdbee1618f58","postedAtISO":"2022-11-27T01:33:28.015Z","deleted":false,"body":"Your approach of making the swaps further away for less-sorted neighbors vaguely reminds me of Comb Sort: https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FComb_sort\n\nWhat if you make it more like comb sort and instead of swapping a further distance only if it thinks it's far off, you instead have a separate phases where *everything* uses a large-distance swap, followed by phases that decrease the swap distance? I'm curious if it would make things faster.","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"701241cf-2a97-4787-85bd-2a24107f7aa6","postedAtISO":"2022-11-27T16:06:18.228Z","deleted":false,"body":"I've never heard of Comb sort before - it's almost surprising that actually works even in 1D!\n\nI'm trying to translate that idea to 2D. So, I'd compare each pixel to every pixel that's an exact radius away, and swap if it's bigger. And then do a bunch of passes until the radius is 1 pixel away. Perhaps Euclidean distance instead of a radius would be easier to implement at first...\n\nCool idea! Thank you for your thoughts!","children":[],"postId":406823,"inReplyTo":"1f5c0ceb-e168-4353-b9dc-fdbee1618f58","hasCohostPlus":false,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":38578,"handle":"z